German

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From Middle High German wale, from Old High German wala, from Proto-West Germanic *walu, from Proto-Germanic *walą.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /vaːl/
  • Audio (Austria):(file)
  • Audio (Germany (Berlin)):(file)
  • Rhymes: -aːl
  • Homophone: Wal
  • Hyphenation: Wahl

Noun

[edit]

Wahl f (genitive Wahl, plural Wahlen)

  1. choice, selection
    eine Wahl treffen. ― to make a choice.
    eine hervorragende Wahl. ― a great choice.
  2. election (process of choosing a leader or representatives)
  3. quality level

Usage notes

[edit]
  • For the distinction between Wahl and Abstimmung, see abstimmen § Usage notes.

Declension

[edit]
Declension of Wahl [feminine]
singular plural
indef. def. noun def. noun
nominative eine die Wahl die Wahlen
genitive einer der Wahl der Wahlen
dative einer der Wahl den Wahlen
accusative eine die Wahl die Wahlen
